stylometry: @Risk allows you to run the same simulation several time simultaneously, using a different value for your input variable which is the decision variable.You can specify any range of cells to run the simulation with.With @RiskSimTable it lets you runs 5 inputs of 1000 iterations each, eahc giving you different simulated results such as the mean, minimum, maximum and standard deviation for those amounts. Example would order quanities and what the expected outcome would be to maximize profit based on production level. you would put in =@RISKSIMTABLE({100,150,200,250,300}) and it would run these inputs simultaneously to show results. also it shows the results graphically easily seeing the mean and standard deviation. The graphs allow you see trends and forecast and pick a best solution.
